{{Infobox company | name = Engels Maps Inc. | logo = [[Asterisk|*****]] | type = [[Private company|Private]] | foundation = [[Fort Thomas, KY]] (1994) | founder = [[Judson Engels]], [[Nathan Engels]] | location = [[Fort Thomas, Kentucky]] | industry = [[publishing]], [[travel]], [[transportation]] | products = [[map]]s, [[atlas]]es, | homepage = [http://engelsmaps.com engelsmaps.com] }}
'''Engels Maps''' is a map company in the [[Ohio Valley]] with particular concentration on the [[Cincinnati metropolitan area|Cincinnati]]-[[Dayton metropolitan area|Dayton]] region.<ref>http://engelsmaps.com engelsmaps.com</ref> It also produces [[chamber of commerce]] maps.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://webonastick.com/maps/1997-nky-engels/|title= Map of Northern Kentucky, Engels Maps, 1997}}</ref>
==Publications==
It has three semi-annual publications that form its foundation: *''Cincinnati Engels Guide'' *''Dayton Engels Guide'' *''Indianapolis Engels Guide'' Their maps are also found in the [[Cincinnati Bell Yellow Pages]] and the [[Dayton WorkBook]].
== Corporate history == Engels Maps was founded by [[Judson Engels]] in 1994.<ref>http://engelsmaps.com engelsmaps.com</ref>
