{{Italic title}}
The '''''Journal of Schenkerian Studies''''' ({{ISSN|1558-268X}}) is a [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] specializing in [[music theory]] and [[musical analysis|analysis]], with a particular focus on [[Schenkerian analysis]]. It is published by the Center for Schenkerian Studies at the [[University of North Texas College of Music]]. The journal is run by graduate students at the center.<ref>[http://mhte.music.unt.edu/journal-schenkerian-studies ''Journal of Schenkerian Studies''] Home page</ref> Its first issue was published in 2005, under [[editor-in-chief]] Jennifer Sadoff. It is currently edited by Colin Davis.

