{{Expand Polish|Stanisław Urbańczyk|date=November 2015}} '''Stanisław Urbańczyk''' (1909–2001) was a [[Poland|Polish]] linguist and academic, a professor at the universities of [[Nicolaus Copernicus University in Toruń|Toruń]], [[Adam Mickiewicz University in Poznań|Poznań]] and [[Jagiellonian University|Kraków]]. He was the head of the Institute of the Polish Language at the [[Polish Academy of Sciences]] in 1973–79.<ref>https://www.ijp-pan.krakow.pl/en/historia-instytutu</ref>
Stanisław Urbańczyk was born in a peasant family of Kwaczała. He completed 4-class elementary school in Kwaczała and started learning in St. Anne's Secondary School (today I Liceum Ogólnokształcące im. Bartłomieja Nowodworskiego w Krakowie). In the years 1929-1934 he studied Polish and Slavic philology<ref>[http://portalwiedzy.onet.pl/16235,,,,urbanczyk_stanislaw,haslo.html Urbańczyk Stanisław]</ref> at the [[Jagiellonian University]]. In 1937 he became an academic teacher. Among his students was young Karol Wojtyła, later the pope [[John Paul II]]. In 1939 he was arrested by the Nazis during [[Sonderaktion Krakau]] and imprisoned in concentration camps in [[Sachsenhausen concentration camp|Sachsenhausen]] and [[Dachau]].<ref>[http://rep.up.krakow.pl/xmlui/bitstream/handle/11716/1208/profesor_stanislaw_urbanczyk_i_t_zarebina_maria_000191.pdf?sequence=1&isAllowed=y Maria Zarębina, Profesor Stanisław Urbańczyk i tajne nauczanie w Uniwersytecie Jagiellońskim (in Polish)]</ref>
He is the author of many books, articles and reviews. Among his scholarly interests were synchronical and diachronical Polish grammar, dialectology, history of language, [[Slavic mythology|Slavic native religion and mythology]], biblical translation and influence of Czech unto Polish in [[Middle Ages]].
==Work== : (A selection) * ''Religia pogańskich Słowian'' (''Religion of Pagan Slavs'', 1947) * ''[http://bazhum.muzhp.pl/media//files/Pamietnik_Literacki_czasopismo_kwartalne_poswiecone_historii_i_krytyce_literatury_polskiej/Pamietnik_Literacki_czasopismo_kwartalne_poswiecone_historii_i_krytyce_literatury_polskiej-r1953-t44-n1/Pamietnik_Literacki_czasopismo_kwartalne_poswiecone_historii_i_krytyce_literatury_polskiej-r1953-t44-n1-s196-215/Pamietnik_Literacki_czasopismo_kwartalne_poswiecone_historii_i_krytyce_literatury_polskiej-r1953-t44-n1-s196-215.pdf Głos w dyskusji o pochodzeniu polskiego języka literackiego, 1953.] * ''Zarys dialektologii polskiej'' (An Outline of Polish Dialectology'', 1962) * ''Encyklopedia wiedzy o języku polskim'' (''The Encyclopaedia of Knowledge about Polish Language'', 1978, as the editor in chief) * ''Dawni Słowianie: wiara i kult'' (Old Slavs - Faith and Cult, 1991) * ''Z miłości do wiedzy: wspomnienia'' (Out of Love to Knowledge - Memoirs, 1997)
